 , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Nevil","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Newill","meanings":["English and Irish (or Norman origin): variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Nevill","meanings":["English and Irish: of Norman origin, a variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Nevels","meanings":["English and Scottish (Wigtownshire): of Norman origin, a variant of   Neville  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Dutch and North German: unexplained."]},{"name":"Nee","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot, John Patrick.","Irish (Galway): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Niadh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Nia</i>’ or <b>Mac Niadh</b> ‘son of <i>Nia</i>’. Compare   McNee  .   Needham   2 and   Neville   have also been adopted as Anglicized forms of this name.","North German: possibly a relationship name from Middle Low German <i>neve</i> ‘nephew, grand-child’."]}]},{"name":"Cecily","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular English form of   Cecilia ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecilie","meanings":["Medieval vernacular English form of   Cecilia ."]},{"name":"Cicely","meanings":["Variant of   Cecily .  This was a common form of the name in the Middle Ages, and in the 20th century was well known as the name of the British actress and singer  Cicely Courtneidge  (  1893–1980 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":51,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Cecily Neville was born in 1404, in Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England. She had at least 1 daughter with Richard Plantagenet. She died in 1479, in England, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1404–1479":"1404–1479","1411–1460":"1411–1460","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1404":"1404","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1411":"1411","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1449":"1449","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","England":"England","Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1404–1479":"1404–1479","1411–1460":"1411–1460","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1404":"1404","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1411":"1411","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1449":"1449","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","England":"England","Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1404–1479":"1404–1479","1411–1460":"1411–1460","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1404":"1404","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1411":"1411","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1449":"1449","London, Middlesex, England":"Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Cecily Neville est née en 1404, à Ewelme, Oxfordshire, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Richard Plantagenet. Elle est décédée en 1479, à Angleterre, à l’âge de 75 ans."},"de":{"1404–1479":"1404–1479","1411–1460":"1411–1460","1449–1491":"1449–1491","1404":"1404","1479":"1479","1455":"1455","1411":"1411","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1449":"1449","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","England":"England","Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Cecily Neville wurde 1404 in Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England geboren. Sie hatte mit Richard Plantagenet mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1479 im Alter von 75 Jahren in England."},"ht":{"1404–1479":"1404–1479","1411–1460":"1411–1460","1449